Commentary Text: Boult to Ashwin, out Caught by Krunal Pandya!! Sensational catch from Krunal. No gas from Ashwin as he lofts this straight down the ground right off the cue-end of his bat. Skies it up and two fielders were converging - Pollard from long-on and Pandya from long-off. Krunal was desperate to gobble it, so flew himself across so quickly and swallowed it air-borne. Top stuff from the senior Pandya. Third wicket for Boult. Ashwin c Krunal Pandya b Boult 12(9) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Bumrah to Harshal Patel, out Lbw!! Huge appeal and one more wicket to Bumrah. Patel is reluctant to leave the field but he has no choice because DC have exhausted their reviews. Oh well, this looks like a poor call from umpire Paul Reiffel. On first viewing looked too high and Patel must've also felt the same. Good length delivery that straightens a wee bit at full pace. Patel is opened up as he misses it. It beats the inside edge and raps him on the back thigh. The impact was in-line but looked too high and would've missed the stumps IMO.Harshal Patel lbw b Bumrah 5(9) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Shreyas Iyer, out Stumped!! A wicket against the run of play and you sensed it, something was coming. With Pant too struggling at the other end, Iyer had to take the risk and unfortunately it doesn't work for him. Chahar gives superb flight on this leg-break, tempted the batsman with the guile and got some bite off the pitch as it breaks away past Iyer's attempted downtown swing. So, what happens next is, the DC captain loses his balance lifting his back feet in the air for a while. QdK spots it, is very alert and whips the bails off in a flash. The foot stayed in the air and it was all over for Iyer. A wicket in the first over for Chahar. Fantastic! Shreyas Iyer st de Kock b Rahul Chahar 25(29) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Boult to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by de Kock!! Boult has sent back both openers now - a nothing shot from Shaw, his bad run never seems to end. Backed away to a short ball, the shot was on, but he went too hard on the pull, played it a fraction too early as well, got a fat top-edge that went straight up. de Kock called for catch, the ball did swivel across in the air, but he kept his eyes on it and completed a fine take. The Capitals in early trouble once again. Prithvi Shaw c de Kock b Boult 10(11) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Boult to Dhawan, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! A duck for Dhawan or is it? They're going to check for the legality of the catch, the soft signal is OUT. Did the ball go straight into the hands? Or did it bounce in front of the fielder? The third umpire is having several looks. Can't tell anything conclusively. He's happy with what he has seen, Dhawan is OUT. Second successive duck for Dhawan, he had successive hundreds as well - on a good length and wide of off, Dhawan saw the width and went hard on the drive, sliced it in the air and towards Suryakumar at backward point. The ball was dying onto him, but Surya acrobatically threw himself forward, got underneath the ball and held on. Dhawan c Suryakumar Yadav b Boult 0(2)
